examples.en: A liquid seeks its own level.
A politician seeks a lot of exposure.
The Danube ... seeks an Orient sea!
She always seeks to do good in the world.
The government study seeks to define urban poverty.
The church seeks to cooperate closely with local schools.
Attractive woman, 27, seeks male, 25-35, for fun and friendship.
The FBI seeks to question these people about the airport bombing.
The report seeks to relate the rise in crime to an increase in unemployment.
The pacific temper seeks to settle disputes on grounds of justice rather than by force.
Another writer who seeks to give expression to popular oral culture is Jose Maria Arguedos.
